transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I was calling to cancel my account and I sent an email and it told me to call this number.

Speaker 2: Also.

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Donald Farrow in Hacienda Heights, California.

Speaker 1: Yes sir.

Speaker 2: Gotcha.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: We have everybody called in because a lot of dudes' wives try to email us and say—

Speaker 1: Yeah, come to find out, dude never wants to cancel so it's always better to just call—

Speaker 2: In.

Speaker 1: With your situation Donald, are you just overstocked right now and need to pump brakes for a while?

Speaker 2: Yeah, but I'm getting a little bit older and I think I'm past what I have right now to—

Speaker 1: Be honest with you.

Speaker 2: I don't think I'll be, I think I'll use up what I have and that'll be the end of it.

Speaker 1: That'll be the end of it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: As a VIP member here, you do have a perk.

Speaker 2: One of them is being able to pause everything for six months at a time, that way they stop—

Speaker 1: Coming monthly.

Speaker 2: It would only be like once or twice a year so that's an option that you have on the table—

Speaker 1: If you ever want to just keep the prescription alive and in your back pocket if and when—

Speaker 2: You do need it.

Speaker 1: And then I can just, I can call you at this number?

Speaker 2: Yeah, exactly.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So I can see that right now if you'd like.

Speaker 1: No, that's okay.

Speaker 2: I'll call back if I have to.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Fair enough.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I hope you have a great rest of your day.

Speaker 2: Thanks a lot.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Take care.
